<paragraph id="8BE64573C5DE5EB608D442FD51E21184" blockId="142.[151,1437,764,1223]" box="[151,497,945,972]" pageId="142" pageNumber="143">Larval host plant(s): unknown.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BE64573C5DE5EB608D44299519211BF" blockId="142.[151,1437,764,1223]" box="[151,385,981,1008]" pageId="142" pageNumber="143">
Figs.: 
<bibRefCitation id="EFC83882C5DE5EB6089E4299516F11BF" author="Clarke, J. F. G." box="[221,380,981,1008]" pageId="142" pageNumber="143" pagination="1 - 8" refId="ref114945" refString="Clarke, J. F. G. (1967) Neotropical Microlepidoptera, XIV. Chilean Microlepidoptera described by Emilio Blanchard. Proceedings of the United States National Museum, 122, 1 - 8. https: // doi. org / 10.5479 / si. 00963801.122 - 3591.1" type="journal article" year="1967">Clarke (1967)</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BE64573C5DE5EB608D442B554A21688" blockId="142.[151,1437,764,1223]" pageId="142" pageNumber="143">
Remarks: The fragment of male genitalia illustrated by 
<bibRefCitation id="EFC83882C5DE5EB60B4442B553B7165B" author="Clarke, J. F. G." box="[775,932,1017,1044]" pageId="142" pageNumber="143" pagination="1 - 8" refId="ref114945" refString="Clarke, J. F. G. (1967) Neotropical Microlepidoptera, XIV. Chilean Microlepidoptera described by Emilio Blanchard. Proceedings of the United States National Museum, 122, 1 - 8. https: // doi. org / 10.5479 / si. 00963801.122 - 3591.1" type="journal article" year="1967">Clarke (1967)</bibRefCitation>
shows the shape of the phallus, with a large, keel-shaped manica. This is a feature typical of 
<taxonomicName id="4C593EF0C5DE5EB60AB74551537E1678" box="[756,877,1053,1079]" class="Insecta" family="Elachistidae" genus="Stephensia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="142" pageNumber="143" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B92D9961C5DE5EB60AB74551537E1678" box="[756,877,1053,1079]" italics="true" pageId="142" pageNumber="143">Stephensia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C593EF0C5DE5EB60BEA455253EC1678" box="[937,1023,1054,1079]" class="Insecta" family="Elachistidae" genus="Perittia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="142" pageNumber="143" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B92D9961C5DE5EB60BEA455253EC1678" box="[937,1023,1054,1079]" italics="true" pageId="142" pageNumber="143">Perittia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, not 
<emphasis id="B92D9961C5DE5EB60C7F455154BD1678" box="[1084,1198,1053,1079]" italics="true" pageId="142" pageNumber="143">
<taxonomicName id="4C593EF0C5DE5EB60C7F455154BA1678" authorityName="Kaila" authorityYear="2019" box="[1084,1193,1053,1079]" class="Insecta" family="Elachistidae" genus="Elachista" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="142" pageNumber="143" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Elachista</taxonomicName>
.
</emphasis>
The illustration also shows the shape of the juxta which is typical of several South American 
<taxonomicName id="4C593EF0C5DE5EB60BBA450E545C1614" box="[1017,1103,1090,1115]" class="Insecta" family="Elachistidae" genus="Perittia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="142" pageNumber="143" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B92D9961C5DE5EB60BBA450E545C1614" box="[1017,1103,1090,1115]" italics="true" pageId="142" pageNumber="143">Perittia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="4C593EF0C5DE5EB60C1E450E55581614" authority="Kaila, 2000" authorityName="Kaila" authorityYear="2000" box="[1117,1355,1089,1115]" class="Insecta" family="Elachistidae" genus="Perittia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="142" pageNumber="143" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="regina">
<emphasis id="B92D9961C5DE5EB60C1E450E54D21614" box="[1117,1217,1090,1115]" italics="true" pageId="142" pageNumber="143">P. regina</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EFC83882C5DE5EB60C8B450D55581614" author="Kaila, L." box="[1224,1355,1089,1115]" pageId="142" pageNumber="143" pagination="159 - 193" refId="ref120391" refString="Kaila, L. (2000) A review of the South American Elachistidae s. str. (Lepidoptera, gelechioidea), with descriptions of 15 new species. Steenstrupia, 25, 159 - 193." type="journal article" year="2000">
Kaila, 
<quantity id="4CA1E896C5DE5EB60D50450D55581614" box="[1299,1355,1089,1115]" metricMagnitude="1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.08" pageId="142" pageNumber="143" unit="in" value="2000.0">2000</quantity>
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
in particular (cf. 
<bibRefCitation id="EFC83882C5DE5EB60901452951EA16CF" author="Kaila, L." box="[322,505,1125,1152]" pageId="142" pageNumber="143" pagination="159 - 193" refId="ref120391" refString="Kaila, L. (2000) A review of the South American Elachistidae s. str. (Lepidoptera, gelechioidea), with descriptions of 15 new species. Steenstrupia, 25, 159 - 193." type="journal article" year="2000">Kaila 2000: 162</bibRefCitation>
). The characterization of the species as ‘brilliant’ is also a trait in 
<emphasis id="B92D9961C5DE5EB60C91452A552F1630" box="[1234,1340,1126,1151]" italics="true" pageId="142" pageNumber="143">
<taxonomicName id="4C593EF0C5DE5EB60C91452A552A1630" box="[1234,1337,1126,1151]" class="Insecta" family="Elachistidae" genus="Perittia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="142" pageNumber="143" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="regina">P. regina</taxonomicName>
.
</emphasis>
The difference in the shape of the lateral extension of the juxta precludes the possibility of these taxa being conspecific. Based on this evidence, 
<taxonomicName id="4C593EF0C5DE5EB6099445E252CB1688" authority="Blanchard" authorityName="Blanchard" box="[471,728,1197,1223]" class="Insecta" family="Elachistidae" genus="Perittia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="142" pageNumber="143" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cupreella">
<emphasis id="B92D9961C5DE5EB6099445E2524C1688" box="[471,607,1197,1223]" italics="true" pageId="142" pageNumber="143">E. cupreella</emphasis>
Blanchard
</taxonomicName>
is here transferred to 
<taxonomicName id="4C593EF0C5DE5EB60B8E45E254301688" box="[973,1059,1198,1223]" class="Insecta" family="Elachistidae" genus="Perittia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="142" pageNumber="143" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B92D9961C5DE5EB60B8E45E254301688" box="[973,1059,1198,1223]" italics="true" pageId="142" pageNumber="143">Perittia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<emphasis id="B92D9961C5DE5EB60C7245E154A21688" bold="true" box="[1073,1201,1197,1223]" pageId="142" pageNumber="143">comb. nov.</emphasis>
</paragraph>
